! STEOM-CCSD STO-3G TightSCF
# Secondary formula test. H2O sto-3g, frozen core = 2 via energy window
# (O1s -20.25 + 2a1 -1.258 frozen; valence -0.594/-0.460/-0.393 active).
# Verify "2 frozen orbitals" in output. COMPLETE active (NActIP 3, NActEA 2).
# Compare ORCA singlet excitation energies to:
#   Python STEOM (eV): [10.804, 12.473, 16.105, 16.478, 22.352, 26.533]
#   EOM-EE-CCSD  (eV): [11.727, 13.761, 16.192, 18.285, 21.171, 27.565]
%method
  FrozenCore FC_EWIN
  EWin -1.0, 10000.0
end
%mdci
  nroots 6
  DoSTEOM true
  DoCISNat false
  NActIP 3
  NActEA 2
end
* xyz 0 1
O    0.000     0.000     0.127
H    0.000     0.758    -0.509
H    0.000    -0.758    -0.509
*
